ta-áš-ta-na-me a-ma-kam ki-ma a-na-kam ma-tum8 da-al-ha-at-ni ú KÙ.BABBAR da-nu-ni : a-dí ki-a-am a-na-kam wa-ar-ha-am iš-té-en6 ú šé-na ù uš-ta-as-hi-ru-ni um-ma a-na-ku-ma KÙ.BABBAR ku-un-kà-ma lá-ma a-na sí-kà-tim tù-ṣa-ni lá-at-bé-ma lá-ta-lá-ak-ma iš-tí-ku-nu lá a-sà-ke-er ú-ma-am iš-tú Ša-lá-tù-a-ar a-na si-kà-tim ni-tí-ṣí a-hi a-ta be-lí a-ta i-na tù-a-ar si-kà-tim a-wi-li a-na-hi-id-ma KÙ.BABBAR ú-ša-ak-na-šu-nu ||| You keep hearing there, that due to the country being in upheaval here, and silver being expensive, for that reason they have caused me to delay here at least a couple of months. I said: 'Put the silver under seal, and before you (sg.) leave for the sikkātum, I will set off and come, so that I do not get separated from you (pl.)'. Today we will go out to the sikkātum from Šalatuwar. Dear brother: when the sikkātum returns, I will take care of the men and produce the money for them.
a-dí sí-kà-tim i-tù-ra-ni-ni a-na Ša-lá-[tù-ar] a-ṣé-er I-na-[-<gap>-(<gap>)] i-ru-[<gap> ] ||| Until the sikkātum returns, <gap> to Šalatuwar to Ina<gap>
