a-ki-di-i Ia tu-se-la-ni su-ma a-na ma-ti-ka e-ti-qu-nim lu ta-du-nu-ni-a-ti-ma lu ni-du-ku ||| You must not let any Akkadians come up to you. If they come to your country, you must hand them over to us so that we may kill them.
ki-ma a-wa-at na-ru-a-im DUMU A-sur su-um-su KU.GI a-na a-ki-di-im a-mu-ri-im u su-bi-ri-im ma-ma-an Ia i-da-an sa i-du-nu u-lci i-ba-la-at ||| In accordance with the words of the stele, a citizen of Assur may not pay any gold to an Akkadian, anAmorite, or a Subarean. The one who does pay (in gold) will not live
Eb-la-i-u ma-<du>-tum i-li-ku-ni-ma URUDU ma-dum i-na E. GAL-lim i-iii-qi-i/5-su-nu-ti-ma KU.BABBAR 2 113 ma-na.TA a-mu-ra-am u-ta-e-ru a-di 10 u4-me URUDU-su i-ga-mu-ru KU.BABBAR a-sa-a-rna u-se-ba-lam ||| Many Eblaites have come here, a lot of copper has been paid out to them in the palace, which they converted at the rate of2 1/3 minas of (copper) per (shekel) of checked silver. Within 1 0 days they will use up their copper. I will then buy silver and have it sent to you.
ša-ma-ku i-nu-mi lu-qu-tum a-ni-tum u-ṣi-a-ni u4-mu-u ka-šu A-bu-ša-lim iš-ti ma-ma-an i-na a-hi-ni ša u-šal-kí-ma-šu-ni pi-iq-da-šu-ma lu-ša-am šu-ma u4-mu-u e-mu-u la u-ṣi-a-am ||| If the days are cold when this merchandise leaves (Assur), you must entrust Abu-salim in the care whichever of our brothers that can bring him safely here, and then let him depart with (him). But if the days are hot he must not depart.
ni-ša-me-ma ru-ba-um it ru-ba-tum a-ba-u-ni be-lu-u-ni a-tú-ni be-lu-ni ki-ma ma-tum sa-hi-at-ni a-na ša-ri-ku-nu ni-iš-pu-ra-am ||| We heard that the king and the queen [ <gap> ]. Dear fathers and lords, our lords: since the land was in turmoil, we wrote to you to put you straight.
li-ba-ka ța i-la-mi-in la li-bi4 DINGIR-ma pi-ri-tum i-li-bi ma-tim i-si-ki-ma a-si-a-ti I ITU u 2 ITU ak-ta-ta a-di ma-tum is-li-mu it ši-ti KU.BABBAR-pi-ku-nu is-ti a-li-ki wa-ar-ki-u-tim u-še-ba-la-kum ||| Do not be angry. Alas, fear is placed in the heart of the land, and for that reason I have been held back for a couple of months. As soon as the land settles down, I will send the rest of your money with the first travellers (leaving).
i-na su-ku-ur-tim a-na ni-si-a ba-lu-[um I 1/2 ma-na KU.BABBAR E nu-a-e a-si-ma ||| To keep my people alive during the blockade, I took out a loan of 1 1/2 shekels of silver from the house of a native Anatolian.
si-ti AN.NA-ka ki-ma si-ka-tu-ni a-di-ni na-di i-na tu-wa-ar si-ka-tim AN.NA-ka a-da-ma a-ta-be-a-ma a-ta-la-kam si-ka-tum da-na a-di tu-wa-ar ka-ni-si-im ra-ma-ka sa-~e-er la te-ra-ba-am ||| Since there is sikkatum, the rest of the tin remains stored. When the sikkatum returns I will sell you your tin, and then I will get up and leave. The sikkatum is fierce. Take care of yourself, and do not enter until the return of the Kane site (king).
ta-as-ta-na-me a-ma-kam ki-ma a-na-kam ma-tum8 da-al-ha-at-ni u KU.BABBAR da-nu-ni a-di ki-a-am a-na-kam wa-ar-ha-am is-te-en6 u se-na u us-ta-as-hi-ru-ni um-ma a-na-ku-ma KU.BABBAR ku-un-ka-ma la-ma a-na si-ka-tim tU-C?a-ni !a-at-be-ma la-ta-la-ak-ma is-ti-ku-nu la a-sa-ke-er u-ma-am is-tu Sa-la-tu-a-ar a-na si-ka-tim ni-ti-C?i a-hi a-ta be-li a-ta i-na tu-a-ar si-ka-tim a-wi-li a-na-hi-id-ma KU.BABBAR u-sa-ak-na-su-nu wa-ar-ha-am is-te-en6 la ta-ha-da-ar ||| You keep hearing there, that due to the country being in upheaval here, and silver being expensive, for that reason they have caused me to delay here at least a couple of months. I said: 'Put the silver under seal, and before you (sg.) leave for the sikkatum, I will set off and come, lest I get blocked up with you (pl.).' Today we will go out to the sikkatum from Salamuwar. My dear brother and lord: when the sikkatum returns, I will take care of the men and produce the money for them. You should not worry about a single month.
ma-tum sa-hi-at-ni ||| the land is in turmoil
is-te-ni-i!i 4 GU 20 ma-na AN.NA ku-nu-ku !ia a-limki I me-at 69 ku-ta-nu 8 ANSE sa-fri-mu u it-nu-stl-nu mi-ma «mi-ma» a-nim i-na Ha-hi-im ku-nu-ki-a a-na A-la u },fi-ti ap-qi-id ||| In total: 4 talents and 20 minas of tin under the seal of the City, 169 kutanumkutānum textiles, 8 black donkeys and their harness- all of this I have entrusted to Alia and Miti in Hahhum under my seal.
i-na Ha-hi-im i-na e-la-i-a AN.NA a-ni-am sa i-qa-ti-a i-ba-!ii-zl a-na A-sa-nim sa KU.BABBAR-pi-su a-.5a-qaf-su-um ||| In Hahhum, on my way up (into Anatolia), I will sell this tin, which I have at my disposal, to Asanum for his silver.
a-na A-sur-e-mu-qi qi-bi-ma um-ma Ma-:jf-i-li-ma 4 GU AN.NA u it-ra-su ku-nu-ki sa A-limk; na-as-a-kum 2 me-at u 50 TUG.HI.A sA.BA 20 TUG.HI.A SIGS 17 TUG.HI.A SIGS sa ik-ri-bi-kG l3 e-ma-ru !)a-la-mu mi-ma a-ni~l a-ra-de8-a-kum lu-qu-ut-ka sal-rna-at e-ma-ru-ka sal-mu-it mi-ma li-ba~ka la,i-pa-ri-id i-hi-id-ma 1 ma-na KU.BABBAR a-pa-ni-a a-na Ha-hi-im !ie-bi-lam su-ma a-bi4 a-ta sa 5 GlN KU.BABBAR sa-ha-ar-tam sa-a-rna i-ku-nu-ki-kG : ku-nu-uk-ma a-pa-ni-a se-bi-lam i-na E-lu-hu-ut ni-ta-:ja-am ||| To Assur-emuqi from Ma~i-ili. I am carrying 4 talents of tin and extras sealed in the City. 250 textiles- thereof 20 textiles of good quality, and 17 textiles of good quality belonging to your ikribum- as well as 13 black donkeys, all of this I am bringing to you. Your goods are well. Your donkeys are well. Do not worry about a thing. Take care and send 1 mina of silver in advance of me to Hahhum. If you are my father, buy 5 shekels of silver worth of small goods, seal it with your seal, and send it to me. We have just left Eluhhut.
is-tu a-limki 5 sa-ri-de8 a-na ig-ri a-na ta-si-a-tim a-di Ha-hi-im a-gu5-ur is-tit Ha-hi-im a-na a-limk; i-tu-nt a-na-kam ma-la :ju-ha-ru e-ru-bu-ni a-na pa-ni-a a-na sa-ra-dim ||| I hired 5 packers for transport from the City until Hahhum. They returned from Hahhum to the City. Here [you should return] all the retainers who enter (Kanes) to me to act as packers.
