a-na-kam A-da-da iš-ti A-šur-DUG DUMU A-zu-za-a i-Sa-la-ah-šu-wa i-mi-ig-ru-ma a-na Ku-ša-ra A-da-da a-na a-wi-lim ta-mu-um re-el-ti-ti-iq ma-mi-tam iš-ti a-wi-lim i-la-qe ma-l zi lu-qu-tam ša DUMU A-zu-za-a-ma ha-ra-an su-qa-ni-ma i-ša-la-ah ||| Here Adada agreed with Assur-tab son of Azuzaya in Salahsuwa, and Adada has travelled to Kussara to have the man swear an oath. He will get an oath from the man and then he will dispatch the goods of Azuzaya's son on the Narrow Track.
1/3 ma-na 2 [GiN] KU.GI ša S[a'-la-ah-šu-a] SIG1 DIRIG Bu-[ <gap> ] a-na 1-ku-pi-[A-šur'] i-ša-qal DU[B'-pa-am ša]l/3 ma-na KU.GI ša ku-nu-ki-[šu] u-ša-ar-šu-[um] šu-ma KU.GI ša Sa-la-ah-su-a ta nu-uš-te-hi-lam 3 ma-na 6 GiN K[U.BABBAR] i-ša-qal-su-um ||| Bu[ <gap> ] will weigh out 1/3 mina and 2 shekels of gold of extra good quality of S[alahsuwa] to Ikun-pi-[ Assur"']. He (Ikun-pi-[ Assur"]) will (then) set the (debt) tablet of 1/3 mina of gold with his seal free to him. If he does not send him the gold from Salahsuwa, he must pay him 3 minas and 6 shekels of s[ilver] (instead).
a-še-er li-bi la-am-nu KU.BABBAR am-si-ma i-na 5 ma-na 3 1/3 ma-na e-li-a-am a-na-kam-ma u-na-hi-id-ka Lu-be u Su-Hu-bu-ur iš-ti pa-nim-ma ru-ur-da-am i-na 20 u4-me a-na Hu-ra-ma i-li-kam a-na Sa-la-ah-su-a a-šu-mi KU.GI e-ti-iq a-ši-me-ma a-na Hu-ra-ma e-ti-iq-ma a-la-an a-ba-ri-im mi-ma sa-nim la-šu ||| Not only am I furious, but I refined the silver and out of 5 minas only 3 1/3 minas came up! Here I gave you the instruction to send Lube and Su-Hubur here to me right away. Twenty days ago he arrived in Hurama. He travelled to Salahsuwa because of the gold. I heard that he had travelled to Hurama and (that) apart from lead there was nothing.
