a-hi-i a-su-<mi> a-mu-ti-ka KU.BABBAR sa su-mi La-qe-ep it-bu-lu KU.BABBAR a-mu-tim su-re-e sa ta-di-nu-su-ni di-ik a-li-ik-ma da-me-e sa a-hi-a se-e ||| My brother was killed because of your amiitum. The silver that he took away in the name of La-qepum - surely he was killed for the silver for the iron that you gave to him. Go and sue for the blood-money for my brother.
ka-ru-um di-nam i-di-in-ma a-di da-mu sa DUMU Sa-lim-A-sur i-ka-su-du-ni e-ba-ar Ta-wi-ni-a ma-ma-an u-lti i-ka-ba-as it a-na e-ri-is-ti-su lu i-na ra-bi-u-tim lu i-na sa-hu-ru-tim ma-ma-an u-ta i-za-az ||| The Colony passed a verdict that until they acquire the blood money for Salim-Assur's son, no one may go via Tawiniya, and no one, either among the great men or among the small men, may carry out his wishes.
is-tu A-sur-tak-ta-ku E.GAL-lum i-y-bu-tu-ni ITU.2.KAM i-li-ik-ma ka-ru-um a-na E.GAL-lim e-li-rna um-ma ka-ru-um-ma A-sur-tak-la-ku wa-s i-ra mi-ma ar-nam it si-la-ttim la ir-si-a-ku-nu-ti qa-di-ni-ma i-na a-li-ku-nu E be-ram i-su u a-na e-ri-is-ti-ku-nu qa-di-ni-ma i-za-az ||| Two months passed since the palace seized Assur-taklaku and then the Colony went up to the palace and said: 'Free Assur-taklaku. He wished no sin or evil upon you. He has a house among us in your city, and with us, he stands at your service'.
