a-§ar ha-ra-an Ma-li-ta-ma a-[n ]a [Wa ]-ah-su-sa-na i-ta-a[p-te-u] ||| At the place where the Malitta road to Wahsusana opens
is-tit Dur4-hu-mi-it URUDU a-na Pu-ru-us-ha-dim is-ri-id-ma ANSE-su URUDU a-di Wa-ah-su-sa-na is-ri-id-ma i-na ma-ṣa-ra-tim ṣa-ha-ra-an U-la-ma u-ṣe-ṣṣu-nu it a-tir-ra-am ||| He packed the copper (to go) from Durhumit to Purushaddum, and he packed his own donkey to (go) as far as Wahsusana, and then I led them (the remaining donkeys) out with the help of the guard posts on the Ulama road and I returned.
4 GiN.TA KU.BABBAR a-di U-ul-ma-a ni-a-ti da-tum ik-su-ud 5 GiN KU.BABBAR a-na sa-da-dim as-qul 10 GiN KU.BABBAR a-na kG-ri-im as-qul GiN a-di U-ul-ma ik-su-ud-ni-a-ti 1 1/2 GIN.TA KU.BABBAR is-tit Du-ur-hu-mi-it ik-su-ud-ni-a-ti ||| Four shekels per (donkey) came on as fees until Ulama. I paid 5 shekels of silver for the (cart) transport. I paid 10 shekels of silver to the Colony. The (expenses) for us until Ulama amounted to 1 shekel. The (expenses) for each of us from Durhumit amounted to one and half a shekel.
a-na-ku u a-hu-u-a a-di 5-si-su is-ti-su lu i-na Pu-ru-us-ha-dim lu i-na U-la-ma lu i-na Wa-ah-su-sa-na is-ti-su ni-na-me-er ||| I and my brothers have met with him at least five times, in Purushaddum, in Ulama or in Wahsusana.
si-kG-tum ru-qa-ma KU.BABBAR-pu sa-du-u su-ma ta-da-num te-er-ta-ka li-li-kam-ma KU.BABBAR 5 ma-na it 6 ma-na le-pu-us-ma lu-se-bi-la-kum [ ]-na u-sa-lam-ma [1 ma]-na 17 GiN.TA [ ] U-la-ma URUDU it [ ] X i-na [Sa-la-t]u-ar URUDU-um [da-mu]-qu-um 1 ma-na 13 GiN.TA i-za-az su-ma a-na Sa-la-tu-ar u 10 GU a-na U-la-ma a-sa-ri-id e-ma-ri se-ri-a-ma [ e ] 1-[ ma ]-ri la a-sa-qal [is-ti] a-li-ki-im pa-ni-e-ma [te-er-t]a-ka li-li-kam [it e-m ]a-ri et-qam ||| The sikkatum has withdrawn but the silver is delayed. If there is trade, write to me and I will make 5-6 minas of silver and send it to you[ <gap> ] settles down, and[ <gap> the price] of copper in Ulama is 17 shekels per mina, and in Salatuwar good copper is sold at a rate of 13 shekels per mina. If I am to pack 10 talents of copper to Salatuwar or Ulama, then send me some donkeys so that I will not have to buy donkeys. Let your message reach me with the first traveller and make donkeys travel here.
