a-ta u-ta [ta-as]-ta-na-me ki-ma i-na [Sa-la-tu ]-ar si-ka-tu-ni-ma [u i-na] qe-ra-ab a-li-ma [i-na pu-u ]h-ri-su-nu si-hi-tu-ni-ma [<gap> (<gap>) ih]-!a-na-ta a-na hi-[im [<gap> (<gap>)] i-tu-ru-ma ||| Do you not keep hearing that there is sikkiitum in Salatuwar: that inside the city itself their assembly is in revolt, and that[ <gap> ] keeps giving offence and has turned[ <gap> ] to sin
is-ta-pa-ar um-m[a su-ut-ma] a-nama-at Wa-ah-su-s[a-na] mu-uq-ta su-ma [Ia] ta-am-qu-ta is-ti-ku-nu na-ak-ra-ak 1-di-A-sur u 1-bi-ZU si-ip-ru-ni ||| He wrote saying: 'Attack the land of WahSusana. If you do not attack, you are an enemy to us.' Iddin-Assur and Ibbi-Suen were our messengers.
a-ki-di-i la tu-se-la-ni su-ma a-na ma-ti-ka e-ti-qu-nim lu ta-du-nu-ni-a-ti-ma lu ni-du-ku ||| You must not let any Akkadians come up to you. If they come to your country, you must hand them over to us so that we may kill them.
Eb-la-i-u ma-<du>-tum i-li-ku-ni-ma URUDU ma-dum i-na E. GAL-lim i-iii-qi-i/5-su-nu-ti-ma KU.BABBAR 2 113 ma-na.TA a-mu-ra-am u-ta-e-ru a-di 10 u4-me URUDU-su i-ga-mu-ru KU.BABBAR a-sa-a-rna u-se-ba-lam ||| Many Eblaites have come here, a lot of copper has been paid out to them in the palace, which they converted at the rate of 2 1/3 minas of (copper) per (shekel) of checked silver. Within 10 days they will use up their copper. I will then buy silver and have it sent to you.
