i-na su-ku-ur-tim a-na ni-si-a ba-lu-[im I 1/2 ma-na KU.BABBAR E nu-a-e a-si-ma ||| To keep my people alive during the blockade, I took out a loan of 1 1/2 shekels of silver from the house of a native Anatolian.
si-ti AN.NA-ka ki-ma si-ka-tu-ni a-di-ni na-di i-na tu-wa-ar si-ka-tim AN.NA-ka a-da-ma a-ta-be-a-ma a-ta-la-kam si-ka-tum da-na a-di tu-wa-ar ka-ni-si-im ra-ma-ka sa-~e-er Ia te-ra-ba-am ||| Since there is sikkatum, the rest of the tin remains stored. When the sikkatum returns I will sell you your tin, and then I will get up and leave. The sikkatum is fierce. Take care of yourself, and do not enter until the return of the Kane site (king).
