a-dí KÙ.BABBAR ša AN.NA-ki-kà mì-ma li-ba-kà lá i-pá-ri-id KÙ.BABBAR iš-tí a-li-ki ša ša-aq-tù-ni lá ú-šé-bi4-lá-kum i-na na-áp-tù ha-ra-nim ú-šé-ba-lá-kum ||| Regarding the money for your tin, do not worry. I did not have the money sent to you with the travellers who were mugged. When the road opens, I will have it sent to you.
a-du-um URUDU-i-kà a-na ša bi4-lá-tim a-na-ku ù dIM-ṣú-lu-li ni-iš-pu-ur-ma ki-ma sú-ur-pí-li nu ha-ra-na-tim ú-kà-lu-nim a-lá-kam lá im-tù-ú-nim a-na ANŠE.HI.A a-ṣé-er Ì-lí-we-da-ku aš-ta-pár šu-ma ANŠE lá uš-té-ri-am i-a-ú-tum-ma ANŠE.HI.A sú-ri li-id-ni-nu-ma i-a-ú-tim-ma ANŠE.HI.A e-ma-ad ||| Concerning your copper, Adad-ṣulluli and I have sent for porters, but because glazed frost is on the roads, they just refused to go. I have just sent a message to Ili-wedaku for some donkeys; if he does not bring donkey(s) to me, (and) if my own donkeys have regained in strength, then I will load my own donkeys.
u4-ma-am ta-áš-pu-ra-am um-ma a-ta-ma a-mì-nim ha-ra-nam lá tù-ša-ra-am ha-ra-nam [a-na-nu-ma] lu-ší-ir ||| Today you wrote to me, saying: 'Why do you not open the road for me? I will open the road [from here]'.
i-na Pu-ru-uš-ha-dim sí-hi-tum we-dum-ma ú-lá e-ra-áb i-na na-áp-tù ha-ra-nim iš-tí pá-nim-ma e-ra-áb-ma ||| There is turmoil in Purušhaddum. I can not enter entirely on my own. When the road reopens, I will enter without delay, and <gap>
ki-ma sí-kà-tù-ni-ma ù ha-ra-nu-um da-na-at-ni Hu-ut-kà lá aṭ-ru-da-am ki-ma ha-ra-nu-um i-ší-ru-ma a-li-ku pá-ni-ú-tum iš-li-mu-ni-ni ||| Since there is truly a sikkātum and the roads are dangerous, I have not led (the shipment) to Hutka. When the road is free again, I will recompense you (pl.) with the first caravan.
TÚG.HI kà-lá-šu-nu ú ša-na-tim a-na Ì-lí-we-da-ku pì-iq-da-ma ha-ra-an Tur4-hu-mì-it li-is-ri-dam ||| Entrust all their textiles and the other's textiles to Ili-wedaku, so that he can pack them for (the) Durhumit road.
