iš-té-ni-iš 4 GÚ 20 MA.NA AN.NA ku-nu-ku ša a-limki 1 me-at 69 ku-ta-nu 8 ANŠE ṣa-lá-mu ú ú-nu-sú-nu mì-ma «mì-ma» a-nim i-na Ha-hi-im ku-nu-ki-a a-na A-lá ú Mì-tí áp-qí-id ||| In total: 4 talents and 20 minas of tin under the seal of the City, 169 kutānukutānum textiles, 8 black donkeys and their harness – all of this I have entrusted to Alla and Miti in Hahhum under my seal.
i-na Ha-hi-im i-na e-lá-i-a AN.NA a-ni-am ša i-qá-tí-a i-ba-ší-ú a-na A-sà-nim ša KÙ.BABBAR-pì-šu a-ša-qal-šu-um ||| In Hahhum, on my way up (into Anatolia), I will sell this tin, which I have at my disposal, to Asanum for his silver.
a-na A-šùr-e-mu-qí qí-bí-ma um-ma Ma-ṣí-ì-lí-ma 4 GÚ AN.NA ù it-ra-sú ku-nu-ki ša A-limki na-áš-a-kum 2 me-at ù 50 TÚG.HI.A ŠÀ.BA 20 TÚG.HI.A SIG5 17 TÚG.HI.A SIG5 ša ik-ri-bi-kà 13 e-ma-ru ṣa-la-mu mì-ma a-nim a-ra-de8-a-kum lu-qú-ut-kà šál-ma-at e-ma-ru-kà šál-mu-ú mì-ma li-ba-kà la i-pá-ri-id i-hi-id-ma 1 MA.NA KÙ.BABBAR a-pá-ni-a a-na Ha-hi-im šé-bi-lam šu-ma a-bi4 a-ta ša 5 GÍN KÙ.BABBAR sà-ha-ar-tám ša-a-ma i-ku-nu-ki-kà ku-nu-uk-ma a-pá-ni-a šé-bi-lam i-na E-lu-hu-ut ni-ta-ṣa-am ||| To Aššur-emuqi from Maṣi-ili. I am carrying 4 talents of tin and extras sealed in the City. 250 textiles – thereof 20 textiles of good quality, and 17 textiles of good quality belonging to your ikribu – as well as 13 black donkeys, all of this I am bringing to you. Your goods are well. Your donkeys are well. Do not worry about a thing. Take care and send 1 mina of silver in advance of me to Hahhum. If you are my father, buy 5 shekels of silver worth of small goods, seal it with your seal, and send it to me. We have just left Eluhhut.
iš-tù a-limki 5 sá-ri-de8 a-na ig-ri a-na ta-ší-a-tim a-dí Ha-hi-im a-gu5-ur iš-tù Ha-hi-im a-na a-limki i-tù-ru a-na-kam ma-lá ṣú-ha-ru e-ru-bu-ni a-na pá-ni-a a-na sá-ra-dim ||| I hired five packers for transporting from the City until Hahhum. They returned from Hahhum to the City. Here [you should return] all the retainers who enter (Kaneš) to me to act as packers.
1 me-at 10 [+30 k]u-ta-ni kà-a[b-<gap>] 1 GÚ 6 [MA].NA AN.NA ù 5 ANŠE ṣa-al-me mì-ma a-nim ku-nu-ki ša a-bi-ni A-šùr-G[AL] DUMU A-zu-a i-ra-de8-a-ku-nu-tí iš-[tù] a-limki a-dí Ha-hi-im da-tám ta-ší-a-tim ú-ku-ul-tám ig-ri sà-ri-dim ù ga-ma-ar-šu-nu A-šùr-GAL ù DUMU Ma-ni-a ša-bu-ú iš-tù Ha-hi-im a-dí Ka-ni-iš ú-ku-ul-tám ig-ri sà-ri-dim ú ga-ma-ar-šu ša 5 ANŠE ù sà-ri-dim A-šur-GAL DUMU A-zu-a ša-bu a-na a-bi4-i a-wi-tí-a a-na 1 GÚ-tim 2/3 MA.NA.TA AN.NA da-tám iš-tù Ha-hi-im a-dí Kà-ni-iš a-dí-šu-um ||| 140 [<gap>] kutānukutānum textiles, 1 talent and 6 minas of tin and 5 black donkeys – all of this under the seal of our father – Aššur-rabi son of Azua will bring to you. From the City until Hahhum the fees and transport costs, fodder, wages for the packer and their expenses have been paid in full to Aššur-rabi and the son of Manniya. From Hahhum to Kaneš the fodder, the wages for the packer and the expenses for the 5 donkeys and the packer have been paid in full to Aššur-rabi son of Azua. I gave it to him at the rate of 2/3 mina per talent of tin as dātumšadduātum tax from Hahhum until Kaneš.
ší-ta šu-ba-at É A-hu-qar ša Ha-hi-im ša a-pá-at sú-qí-nim ša É Zi-zi-a a-na 6 1/3 MA.NA KÙ.BABBAR ni-iš-a-ma-ku-ma ||| We have bought you a 2 šubat large house for 6 1/3 minas of silver, formerly belonging to Ahuqar in Hahhum, located in the alley across from Ziziya's house
a-ša-me-ma AN.NA-kà ù NA4.GUG i-na Ha-hi-im É I-dì-A-šùr DUMU Da-dì-a i-ba-ší ||| I hear that your tin and carnelian are in the house of Iddin-Assur son of Dadiya in Hahhum
lu-qú-tám ša Ša-lim-A-šur ša i-na Ha-hi-im É I-sú-ri-ik ||| goods belonging to Šalim-Aššur that were in Hahhum in the house of Issu-arik
2 né-pí-ša-an 16 MA.NA KÙ.BABBAR ša A-šùr-re-ṣí 1 né-pí-šum 10 MA.NA KÙ.BABBAR ša Ú-zu-a i-Ha-hi-im i-na-dí ||| 2 packages containing 16 minas of silver belonging to Aššur-reṣi and 1 package containing 10 minas of silver belonging to Uzua in Hahhum
a-ma-lá té-er-tí-a ||| In accordance with my message
a-na Ha-hi-im šu-up-ra-ma ||| you should write to Hahhum that
