ig-ri ANŠE ||| hire of one donkey
ina Ha-hi-im ú-nu-ut-ni ||| In Hahhum we set aside our goods
ha-ra-an sú-qí-nim da-na-at ||| the Narrow Track is difficult
šu-ma iš-tí Tí-me-el-ki-a-e-im ú Ba-ad-na-e-im ta-na-ki-ra-ni ||| If you (pl.) become the enemy of the ruler of Timelkiya or of the ruler of Badna
26 ma-na LÁ 3 GÍN AN.NA a-na É.GAL-lim áš-qúl ||| I paid 26 minas minus three shekels of tin to the palace
1 1/3 ma-na AN.NA a-na ra-dí-im ša ru-ba-tim áš-qúl ||| I paid one and a third mina of tin to the guide of the queen
1/2 ma-na 5 GÍN AN.NA ú sà-he-er-tám a-na ma-li-ki-im ša ru-ba-im a-dí-in ||| I gave half a mina and five shekels of tin and the trinkets to the king's counsellor
