ša bi4-lá-tim li-gu5-ur-ma mì-ma lá i-zi-ba-am ||| he is to hire porters, and not leave anything behind
a-Lu-hu-za-tí-a lu-šé-tí-qam ||| he should let it travel to Luhuzattiya
ki-ma a-Tí-mì-[i]l5-ki-a e-ru-bu tí-ir-⌈tù⌉-šu a-ṣé-ri-kà li-li-kam-ma ra-dí-am iš-tí A-zu e-ri-iš ||| when he enters Timelkiya he should send a message to you, and you should ask for a guide from Azu
a-ṣé-er ⌈A-lá⌉-bi4-im ṭù-ru-sú ||| then you must send him to Ali-abum
Hu-ra-ma-i-um ú Ša-lá-ah-šu-a-i-um ni-is-ha-tim lá i-lá-qé-ú ||| the Huramean and the Šalahšuwean should not levy the nishātumšadduātum tax
5 MA.NA hu-ša-e i-na kà-ṣí-im a-na ta-ší-a-tim iš-tù Qá-ṭa-ra a-di Ha-mì-sá-nim 1/3 MA.NA AN.NA a-ta-ší-a-tim ANŠE uš-pá-il5-ma 1 MA.NA 15 GÍN AN.NA a-pu-ul iš-tù Bu-ra-li-im a-di Bi-ir-tù-im 17 GÍN AN.NA a-na ta-ší-a-tim 7 GÍN AN.NA iš-tù a-al Kà-ni-ší-e a-dí Tí-me-el-ki-a a-na ig-ri e-re-qí-im iš-tù Tí-me-el-ki-a a-di Hu-ur-ma a-na ig-ri ANŠE 2 GÍN KÙ 2 GÍN AN.NA áš-qúl iš-tù Hu-ra-<ma> a-dí Lu-ha-za-tí-a 3 GÍN KÚ.BABBAR 3 GÍN AN.NA a-na ig-ri ANŠE ||| Five minas of scrap metal in the steppe for transport. From Qaṭṭara to Hamizanum 1/3 mina of tin for transport. I replaced a donkey and had to balance 1 mina and 15 shekels of tin. From Burallum to Birtu'um 17 shekels of tin for transport. 7 shekels of tin as hire of a wagon from 'the City of the Kanešeans' to Timelkiya. From Timelkiya to Hurma I paid 2 shekels of silver and 2 shekels of tin for the hire of a donkey. From Hura<ma> to Luhuzattiya I paid 3 shekels of silver and 3 shekels of tin for the hire of a donkey.
1/2 GÍN KÙ.BABBAR i-na Hu-ra-ma a-na É ub-ri a-dí-in 12 GÍN pá-zu-ur-ti TÚG.HI.A i-na Lu-hu-za-tí-a a-na I-ku-pí-a DUMU Da-a-a a-dí-in 3 GÍN AN.NA [a-na ANŠE].HI.A wa-bar-šu [i-na <gap> ] a-dí-in [<gap> GÍN AN.NA] i-tí-tù-ri-im [<gap> GÍN AN.]NA a-na É [wa]-áb-ri i-na ⌈Ša⌉-mu-ha a-dí-in 1 GÍN KÙ.BABBAR a-na ig-ri ša bi4-il5-tim a-dí Ša-mu-ha a-dí-in ||| I paid half a shekel of silver for inns in Hurama. I paid Ikun-piya son of Daya 12 shekels in Luhuzattiya for the smuggling of the textiles. I paid 3 shekels of tin [for the donkey]s (and) his lodging [in GN]. I paid [x shekels of tin] at the bridge. I paid [x shekels of t]in for inns in Šamuha. I paid 1 shekel of silver in wages for the porter until Šamuha.
ŠU.NIGÍN 2 1/2 ma-na KÙ.BABBAR A-sà-nim ub-lá-kum lu i-na Lu-hu-za-tí-a lu i-na Ša-mu-ha-a lu-qú-tám ta-dá-nam ||| In total: 2 1/2 minas of silver was brought to you by Asanum. Sell the goods, be it in Luhuzattiya or in Šamuha.
um-ma Ma-ma-hi-ir-ma a-na A-lá-hi-im qí-bi4-ma šu-ma TÚG.HI.A ša Lu-hu-za-tí-<a> ú-šé-ri-bu-nim lá ú-šé-ri-bu-nim úz-ni pì-té šu-ma ú-šé-ri-bu-ni-šu-nu a-ma-lá ú-ša-hi-zu-kà a-na KÙ.BABBAR ta-er-šu-nu pá-zu-ur-ta-šu-nu 7 1/2 GÍN KÙ.BABBAR 2/3 ma-na KÙ.BABBAR iš-tí En-na-Sú-[in] e-rí-šu-ma 7 1/2 GÍN dí-šu-nu-tí ||| From Man-mahir to Ali-ahum: Inform me whether or not they have brought in the textiles from Luhuzattiya. If they have brought them in, then convert them to silver as I instructed you <gap> Their smuggling (cost) 7 1/2 shekels of silver. They asked for 40 shekels of silver from Enna-Suen, but give them 7 1/2 shekels.
um-ma Ma-ma-hi-ir-ma a-na A-la-hi-im qí-bi-ma a-dí ma-la ù ší-ni-šu tí-ir-tí i-li-kà-kum a-dí-i TÚG.HI.A ša i-na Lu-hu-za-tí-a i-ba-ší-ú-ni šu-ma a-mì-ša-am ù-šé-ri-bu-ni-šu-nu a-ma-lá tí-ir-tí-a a-na KÙ.BABBAR ta-er-šu-nu ||| From Man-mahir to Ali-ahum: I have sent word to you both once and twice concerning the textiles that are in Luhuzattiya. If they have brought them in there (in Kaneš), then convert them to silver in accordance with my instructions.
i-na dUTU-ši ṭup-pí ta-ša-me-a-ni A-lá-hu-um lu a-na Hu-ra-ma lu a-na Ku-ša-ra a-na ṣé-ri-a li-li-kam ||| On the day you hear my letter, Ali-ahum should come and meet me in either Hurama or in Kuššara
i-ša-am-ší ša ṭup-pí-ni ta-ša-me-ú šu-ma na-ṭù-ma a-na Ša-mu-ha ú Ku-ša-ra a-na ṭup-pé-kà lá ta-ša-hu-ut-ma ta-lá-ak ṭup-pè-kà a-na 3-[š]í-šu ma-ha-aṣ-ma i-na pá-ni-kà lu-šé-tí-qú-ma ù a-ta ur!-kà-tám a-lik šu-ma lá na-ṭù-ma a-na Ša-mu-ha ú Ku-ša-ra lá ta-lá-ak ṭup-pí-kà a-na 3-ší-šu ma-ha-aṣ-ma a-na Tí-li-im-ra lu-šé-tí-qú-ma ù a-ta iš-tí ur-ki-ú-tim et-qam ù a-ma-at-kà Sí-li-ma a-na Hu-ra-ma lu-šé-tí-qú-ma ù a-ta [a]-ni-ša-am er!-ba-am ||| I will divide them in three, and let them travel to Tilimra, and then you can travel later yourself. Then they should let your slave-girl Silimma travel to Hurama, so you can come in here yourself.
um-ma a-ta-ma a-na 10 ⌈u4⌉-[me] iš-tù Ku-ša-ra ú-ul iš-tù Ša-mu-ha [ú-šé-ba-lá-kum] šu-ma lá [ú-šé-bi4-lá-kum] šu-ša-a[l-šu-um a-ša-qá-al] ||| You said: 'Within ten days, [I will send it to you] from either Kuššara or from Šamuha. If I do not [send it, I will pay you the] trip[le]'.
a-[na H]a-nu-nu qí-bi4-ma um-ma <<[um]-ma>> A-šur-DU10-ma a-na-kam iš-tí [ṣú]-ha-ri-e ša I-[dí]-Sú-en6 DUMU Ku-ku-lá-nim i-ma-at Za-al-pá ku-ša-[ra-i-ú]-um ma-qí-it-ni-a-tí [mì-m]a a-nim ša KI DU NI [a-n]a Ku-ša-ra e-li-ú-ni-ni [a]-na-ku e-li-ma [<gap> (<gap>)]-e ú ṣú-ha-ra-am [i-na] ba-áb a-bu-li-im [aṣ]-ba-at-ma i-na e-mu-qí <gap> lim ú-bar-ta-am e-pu-uš-ma <gap> e ú ṣú-ha-ra-am a-na É.GAL-lim uš-té-li ú al-pu ší-im-tù-um i-na É.GAL-lim i-za-zu a-na É.GAL-lim a-dí ma-lá ú šé-ni-šu né-li-ma um-ma É.GAL-lúm i-na ša-li-tim i-ma-at Za-al-pá al-qé ||| To Hanunu from Aššur-ṭab: The man of Kuššara has fallen upon us here in the Land of Zalpa together with the servants of Iddin-Su'en son of Kukulanum. [(detailed inventory of shipment)] all this, which <gap> went up to Kuššara, so I also personally went up (there), and I seized [<gap>] and the servant in the city gate, and I forced [<gap>] the Station, and made [<gap>] and the servant go up to the palace, and the marked bulls are standing (there). We went up to the palace several times, but the palace said: 'I took them as booty from the Land of Zalpa'.
