ŠUNIGIN 3 MA.NA 15 GÍN KÙ.BABBAR iš-tù a-limki i-na e-lá-i-šu lu i-na Kà-ni-iš lu i-na Ha-tim a-li e?-mu?-ru?-šu? KÙ.BABBAR Šál-mah a-na I-dí-a-bi4-im i-ša-qal ||| In total, Šalim-ahum must pay 3 minas 15 shekels of silver to Iddin-abum wherever he sees him upon his (return) up from the City, be it in Kaneš or in Hattum.
a-ša-me-ma a-na ku-ta-ni ší-mu-um i-na Kà-ni-iš i-ba-ší ší-ta-lá-ma šu-ma i-na Kà-ni-iški KÙ.BABBAR ù-lá tù-šé-lá-a-nim i-na Kà-ni-iš-ma ku-ta-ni a-na DAM.GÀR lá tù-ša-ra ku-ta-ni lu a-na Ha-tim lu a-na Pu-ru-uš-ha-dim ||| I hear that there is a market for kutānukutānum textiles in Kaneš. Make inquiries, and if you cannot make a profit in Kaneš then you must not release the kutānukutānum textiles on credit to a trader in Kaneš itself. Instead you must bring up my kutānukutānum textiles to either Hattum or to Purušhaddum.
lu i-na Ha-tim lu i-na Pu-ru-uš-ha-dim ||| (Do such and such), be it in Hattum or in Purušhaddum.
a-na-kam ru-ba-um Wa-á-š-ha-na-i-um i-li-kam a-na Pu-ru-uš-ha-dim ù Ha-tim ik-ta-lá-ni ||| The king of Wašhaniya came here. He has prevented us from going to Purušhaddum or Hattum.
ṭup-pá-kà i-li-kam-ma a-šu-mì AN.NA 4 GÍN ša Dan-A-šur i-Kà-ni-iš e-zi-bu mì-ma-ša-ma ú-lá ta-al-tap-tám mì-šu ša ki-ma a-wi-lim ra-gi5-im kà-ku-šu il5-qé-ú-ma a-Ku-na-na-me-et i-tal-ku ta-á-š-pu-ra-am um-ma a-ta-ma a-šu-mì-šu-ma a-Ha-tim a-pá-ri-kà-ma iš-tí-a a-na Pu-ru-uš-ha-dim e-ra-ab-ma ú-za-kà-ma i-pá-nim-ma a-ṭá-ra-da-šu ||| Your letter came, but you wrote nothing at all about the 4 shekels of tin that Dan-Aššur left behind in Kaneš. Why has he taken his weapons like a criminal and gone to Kunanamit? You wrote, saying: 'Because of him, I am barred from going to Hattum so he will enter Purušhaddum with me, and I will clear myself, and then I will send him to you as fast as possible'.
Ištar-lá-ma-sí DUMU.SAL A-šùr-na-da Puzur4-Ištar a-na am-tù-tim e-hu-uz-ma a-na Pu-ru-uš-ha-dim lu a-na Ha-tim a-šar ha-ra-šu-ni iš-tí-šu i-ra-de8-ší ù qá-dí-šu-ma a-na Kà-ni-iš ú-ta-ra-ší šu-ma e-zi-ib-ší 5 MA.NA KÙ.BABBAR i-ša-qal ||| Puzur-Aššur took Ištar-Lamassi daughter of Aššur-nada as secondary wife, and he will take her with him wherever his travels lead him – to Hattum or to Purušhaddum – but he must return her with him to Kaneš. If he deserts her, he must pay 5 minas of silver.
qá-dí-iš-tám i-na Kà-ni-iš ù Ni-ih-ri-a ú-lá e-ha-az ||| He will not take a qadištu-wife in Kaneš or in Nihriya
