iš-tù Tí-me-el-ki-<a> ú-ṣí a-lá-ni ú ša kà-ší-im ša Ku-pì-tá ša pá-ni-šu qé-pá-nim-ma šé-bi4-lá-nim ||| I left Timelkiya. Entrust and send the acorns that are available to him, including those belonging to the kaššum-official of Kupitta
iš-tù qá-áb-li ša-dù-im 10 GÍN.TA A[N.NA] a-na mu-tí-tí-in a-dí Ha-zu áš-qúl iš-tù La-al-ga a-dí Ha-zu 2 mu-tí-ti-in ú e-li-ti[m] 7 1/2 GÍN A[N.NA] áš-qúl iš-tù [Ha]-zú a-dí Ti-mì-il5-ki-a a-na a-wi-le-[én] 5 GÍN.TA AN.NA áš-qúl iš-tú Tí-mì-il5-ki-a a-dí Hu-ra-ma 2 GÍN KÙ.BABBAR 2 GÍN AN.NA áš-qul iš-tù Hu-ra-ma a-dí Kà-ni-iš 6 GÍN KÙ.BABBAR ig-ri ANŠE ||| From the midst of the mountains I paid ten shekels [of tin] each to get two side-packs to Hazu. From Lalga to Hazu I paid 7 1/2 shekel of t[in] for the two side-packs and one top-pack. From Hazu to Timelkiya I paid the two men 5 shekels of tin each. From Timelkiya to Hurama I have paid two shekels of silver and two shekels of tin. From Hurama to Kaneš: 6 shekels of silver for donkey-fodder.
AN.NA ša A-ki-a ub-lá-ni a-na ha-ra-an sú-qí-nim a-na šé-ru-bi-im ú-lá na-ṭù-ú AN.NA-kà i-na Lu-hu-za-tí-a na-dí-i a-na Kà-ni-iš šé-ru-ba-am lá šé-ru-ba-am té-er-ta-kà li-li-kam-ma AN.NA-kà a-šar ma-lá-ki-im mì-li-ik ||| It was not feasible to take the tin that Akiya brought onto the Narrow Track, and so we deposited it in Luhuzattiya. Send us a message whether we should let it enter Kaneš or not, and take a decision (about) where to (take) your tin.
a-na-kam A-da-da iš-tí A-šur-DÙG DUMU A-zu-za-a i-Ša-lá-ah-šu-wa i-mì-ig-ru-ma a-na Ku-ša-ra A-da-da a-na a-wi-lim ta-mu-im ⌈e⌉-tí-tí-iq ma-mì-tám iš-tí a-wi-lim i-lá-qé-⌈ma⌉ ú lu-qú-tám ša DUMU A-zu-za-a-ma ha-ra-an sú-qá-ni-ma i-ša-lá-ah ||| Here Adada agreed with Aššur-ṭab son of Azuzaya in Šalahšuwa, and Adada has travelled to Kuššara to have the man swear an oath. He will get an oath from the man and then he will dispatch the goods of Azuzaya's son on the Narrow Track.
a-na Puzur4-A-šùr DU10-ṣí-lá-A-šùr A-šur-ba-ni dIM-ba-ni ù I-ku-pá-ša qí-bi4-ma um-ma Bu-za-zu-ma ||| To Puzur-Aššur, say: Thus speaks Buzazu
AN.NA iš-tí URUDU-i-ni a-na ba-ru-im lá-šu ||| tin together with copper
AN.NA-ki lu ha-ra-an sú-qí-nim šu-ma na-ṭù-ú lu-šé-ri-bu-nim ||| If it is feasible, I will let the tin enter the Narrow Track
lu ri-ik-sí lu-pí-šu-ma a-na Kà-ni-iš i-na sú-na-tí-šu-nu lu-šé-ri-bu-nim ||| let them make bundles and bring it into Kaneš in their lap
i-na 2 me-at 3[8 TÚG.HI.A] ša šé-ep I-dí-dIM <ša> a-na Né-ša a-na É.GAL-lim e-ru-bu-ni ŠÀ.BA 21 TÚG SIG5 ha-ra-an sú-qí-nim a-na Du-ur-mì-it i-tal-ku ||| Out of 238 textiles of Iddin-Adad that entered the palace in Neša, 21 good textiles have gone off to Durhumit by the Narrow Track
2 GÚ AN.NA ù 11 TÚG.HI.A 1 ANŠE ṣa-lá-ma-am A-šur-ta-ak-lá-ku DUMU Kà-ar-ta-a i-ra-de8-a-ku a-na Kà-ni-ìš ú-lá e-ru-ba-am iš-tù Za-al-pá ha-ra-an sú-qá-ni-ma i-ta-lá-ak ||| Aššur-taklaku son of Kartaya leads 2 talents of tin and 11 textiles (on) one black donkey to you. He did not enter Kaneš, but from Zalpa he went (via) the Narrow Track
um-ma I-na-a-ma a-na A-šur-DÙG ú MAN-A-šur qí-bi-ma a-na-kam ru-ba-um ù ru-ba-tum a-na ha-ra-na-tim ša pá-zu-ur-tim iš-pu-ru-ma um-ma šu-nu-ma ša i-ma-tim TÚG.HI.A ù AN.NA na-áš-ú-ma ša ta-ma-ra-ni ṣa-áb-ta-ma AN.NA ú TÚG.HI.A a-tù-nu kà-i?-lá-ma ra-ga-am i-a-tí ri-id-a ú a-na ša ha-ra-an sú-qí-nim iš-ta-áp-ru a-pu-tum AN.NA ù TÚG.HI.A lá tù-pá-za-ra ú a-na ha-ra-an sú-qí-nim mì-ma lá ta-ša-kà-na a-pu-tum a-wa-tum da-na-at mì-ma e šé-bi4-lá-ma li-ba-ak-nu e im-ra-aṣ ṭup-pá-am ší-ta-me-šu-ma a-na A-šur-DÙG še-bi4-il5-šu ||| Thus says Ina-a, say to Aššur-ṭab and the king's commissioner: the ruler and the ruler's wife sent word to me about the Narrow Track. Thus they said: whoever possesses textiles and tin on the roads that I have seized, tin and textiles they should not carry off, and smuggle it away from me and send it on the Narrow Track road, they sent word to me, saying, 'Goods, tin and textiles, do not smuggle, and on the Narrow Track road anything do not send, lest you be sorry.' A very serious matter, do not send anything, lest you be sorry. Hear the letter carefully and send it to Aššur-ṭab.
ha-ra-ni a-na a-lim ||| to the City
a-wa-at-ku-nu da-na-a ||| your (pl.) messages are strict
ṣa-ah-ru-um a-ri-ni-iš lá e-ra-ba-ni ||| a junior cannot enter
a-na e-ra-bi4-im ni-ip-ta-lá-ah ||| we are very anxious about entering
a-wa-tum ša É.GAL-lim li-id-mi-qá-ma ||| when the orders of the palace soften
a-wa-at kà-ri-im da-na ||| the orders of the Colony are strict
um-ma kà-ru-um Kà-ni-iš-ma ||| Thus says the Kaneš Colony
ha-ra-an sú-qí-nim ||| the Narrow Track
šu-ma Puzur2-A-šùr ha-ra-an sú-qí-nim-ma iš-tí ṣú-ha-ri-šu i-ṭá-ra-ad-kà um-ma a-ta-ma i-pá-ni-šu le-tí-iq-ma i-na Hu-ra-ma ù-lá i-na Ku-ša-ra KÙ.BABBAR X MA.NA iš-tí DAM.GÀR-im lá-al-qé ú KÙ.BABBAR li-dí-šu-nu i-na Hu-ra-ma ú-lá i-na Ku-ša-ra ki-lá ||| If Puzur-Aššur wants to send you by the Narrow Track together with his servants, you tell him: 'Let me travel ahead of him, and let me take an interest-bearing loan of some [x minas] of silver with a merchant in Hurama or in [Kuššara] (and) let him give [the silver] to them'. Hold the [silver] back in [Hurama] or in [Kuššara].
a-na Ku-bu-ur-na-at e-ru-ub-ma Kà-sú-a ú-lá ak-šu-ud i-na ma-at Ta-hu-ru-a wa-ša-áb la-at-bi4-a-ma iš-tù ma-at Ta-ah-ru-a a-na Hu-ra-ma a-tal-kam a-na Ku-bu-ur-na-at šu-up-ra-am ||| I went into Kuburnat, but I did not catch up with Kazua. He is staying in the Land of [Tah]ruwa. Let me set out and come from the Land of [Tahruwa] to Hurama. [Write] to Kuburnat <gap>
šál-ma-ku i-Dur4-hu-mì-it wa-áš-ba-ku i-na Hu-ra-ma 1 ku-ta-nam i-ṣé-ri-a il5-qé iš-tù Hu-ra-ma a-dí Dur4-hu-mì-it 1/2 MA.NA da-tum a-na ANŠE ik-šu-ud ||| I am well. I stay in Durhumit. He took one kutānu-textile on my account in Hurama. The fees from Hurama to Durhumit amounted to half a mina per donkey-load <gap>
lá-ma ku-ṣí-im a-na Pu-ru-uš-ha-tim le-ru-ub na-áb-ri-tum lá i-kà-ša-da-ni ||| I want to enter Purušhaddum before the cold sets in <gap>
a-na DUB.SAR ša šu-bi4-ri-a-ta-am i-ša-me-ú ||| a scribe who understands Šubarian
a-na a-ší-tí-[šu <gap> ] ||| to his wife
ṣú-ha-ru-ú A-sà-nim ša É Ás-qú-dim ú Pì-lá-ah-Ištar DUMU E-lá-ma ha-ra-nam iš-té-ni-iš i-li-ku-nim-ma i-na Hu-ra-ma a-na É Ku-bi-a iš-té-ni-iš e-ru-bu-ma ni-is-ha-tí-šu-nu É.GAL-lúm iš-té-ni-iš i-sú-ùh i-na wa-ar-ki-tim lu-qú-tum i-ṣí-bi-it-ma lu-qú-tám ša A-sà-nim É.GAL-lúm i-ta-ba-al ||| Asanum's servants of the house of Asqudum and Pilah-Ištar son of Elamma travelled jointly, and in Hurama they entered the house of Kubiya jointly, and the palace levied their nishātušadduātum tax from them jointly. Later the goods were confiscated, and the palace has taken away Asanum's belongings
ANŠE-ri i-sí-kà-tim it-ru-ú-ma a-pa-ṭá-ri-šu-nu 5/6 ma-na AN.NA áš-qúl ||| They took my donkeys out for the sikkātum and I paid 50 shekels of tin to redeem them
il5 um-ma Ha-ší-im-na-wa-ar-ma 2 na-ru-qé-en6 al-qé-ma 13 TÚG dar-ku e-<lá> 13 TÚG ù 1 ra-qí-tim mì-ma ú-lá ub-lu-nim ší-tí TÚG.HI.A ša Hu-ra-ma i-pá-ni-kà áb-kam ||| Thus (spoke) Hashimnawar: The two bolts of red cloth which he did not bring, (these) 13 cloths and one further item which he brought, the textiles of Hurama came into your possession
i-n[u-m]ì a-na Tí-me-el-ki-a a-ṣé-er lu-qú-tim e-tí-qú 1/3 MA.NA KÙ.BABBAR a-sà-he-er-tim 10 GÍN KÙ.BABBAR a-É ub-ri 5 GÍN KÙ.BABBAR É wa-á[b-r]i i-na Ša-lá-ah-šu-a 5 GÍN KÙ.BABBAR É u[b-ri] i-Hu-ra-ma 6 GÍN KÙ.BABBAR a-na kà-ší-im i-H[u-r]a-ma 1/2 GÍN KÙ.BABBAR ú-qá-li-lá-ni ||| When I travelled to Timelkiya to meet up with the goods: a third mina of silver for sun-dries. Ten shekels of silver for inns: Five shekels of silver for inns in Šalahšuwa (and) five shekels of silver for inns in Hurama. 6 shekels of silver for the official in Hurama – he fooled me out of half a shekel of silver.
AN.NA a-na e-ba-a[r] Ša-la-ah-šu-wa lá ú-šé-tù-qú ki-ma ša-lá-am AN.NA-ki e-ba-ar Tí-me-el-ki-a-ma AN.NA a-na Dur4-hu-mì-id lu-šé-tí-qú ||| do not let them send the tin via Šalahšuwa. For the safety of my tin, they should let the tin travel via Timelkiya to Durhumit
a-na A-da-da ša Ša-lá-ah-šu-wa ||| To Adada of Šalahšuwa
a-ṣé-er li-bi4 lá-am-nu KÙ.BABBAR am-sí-ma i-na 5 MA.NA 3 1/3 MA.NA e-li-a-am a-na-kam-ma ú-na-hi-id-kà Lu-be ú Šu-Hu-bu-ur iš-tí pá-nim-ma ṭù-ur-da-am i-na 20 u4-me a-na Hu-ra-ma i-li-kam a-na Ša-la-ah-šu-a a-šu-mì KÙ.GI e-tí-iq áš-me-ma a-na Hu-ra-ma e-tí-iq-ma a-lá-an a-ba-ri-im mì-ma ša-nim lá-šu ||| Not only am I furious, but I refined the silver and out of 5 minas only 3 1/3 minas came up! Here I gave you the instruction to send Lube and Šu-Hubur here to me right away. Twenty days ago he arrived in Hurama. He travelled to Šalahšuwa because of the gold. I heard that he had travelled to Hurama and (that) apart from lead there was nothing.
a-dí sú-ú-um lá šar-ma-at-ni a-wi-lúm i-na Ša-la-ah-šu-wa ú-ša-áb a-dí 10-šu áš-ta-pár-šu-um i-lá-kam i-ša-ra-am-ší-ma a-na Ha-tim a-ta-lá-ak ||| As for the fact that the su'um-stone has not yet been cut up: the man is still staying in Šalahšuwa. I have written to him at least ten times. If he comes here and cuts it I can go to Hattum.
šu-ma a-na Ha-hi-im ta-pá-lá-ah a-na Ur-šu-ma a-li-ik a-pu-tum a-pu-tum we-dí-kà-ma a-li-ik iš-tí ILLAT a-na Ma-ma lá té-ra-áb ù ma-lá té-er-tí a-limki ILLAT-at a-hi-kà a-na šál-ší-šu li-pè-er-sú-ma pá-ni-ú-um-ma i-Ma-ma lu-ṣí-ma a-na-ma ma-at Kà-ni-iš ik-šu-du ša-ni-um i-na Ur-šu lu-ṣí ù ša-li-iš-tum ki-a-ma lu-ṣí ||| If you are afraid (to go) to Hahhum, then go to Uršu instead. Please, please! Go alone! Do not enter Mamma together with the caravan. Further, in accordance with the orders of the City assembly your brother's caravan must be divided into three parts, so that the first may leave Mamma, and as soon as it has reached the land of Kaneš, then the second will leave Uršu. The third can then leave in the same way.
ma-tí-i-a im-qú-ta-ma ||| the land has fallen
a-lá-né-e-a úh-ta-li-iq ||| I destroyed the (enemy's) troops
al-pí-šu-nu ú ṣé-ni-šu-nu il5-té-qé ||| I took their cattle and their flocks
ru-ba-um me-et-ma hu-ha-ra-am al-té-qé ||| the prince died and I took the booty
ma-tí-i-a na-ṣa-ri-im ú li-bi-im ta-da-nim ||| my land was protected and my heart was relieved
ma-tí-i iš-ta-ra-áp ú qú-ut-ra-am ub-ta-i-iš ||| I burnt the land and made it desolate
i-na-ar a-lam Ha-ar-sá-am-na ||| in the city of Harsama
ma-tí-i a-na ma-tí-kà im-qú-tám-ma ||| the land fell to your land
al-pá-am ú-lu ṣé-na-am iš-qí-it ||| I acquired cattle or sheep
lu ni-it-ma ma-mì-tum pá-ni-tum e-ṣa-at ||| the former oath was broken
