šu-ul-mu-um i-na Pu-ru-uš-ha-dim Ú-lá-ma ma-mì-tám iš-tí Pu-ru-uš-ha-dim il5-té-qé ||| There is peace in Purušhaddum. Ulama has accepted the oath with Purušhaddum.
mì-ma a-wa-tim ša Kà-ni-iš [P]u-ru-uš-ha-tim Ú-lá-ma Ú-ša ša ki-ma ta-áš-me-a-ni [i]-na ṭup-pí-im [lu-up]-ta-nim [ú iš-tí a-li-ki-im pá-ni-e-ma té-er-ta-kà li-li-kam] ||| Write any news you hear from Kaneš, Purušhaddum, Ulama or Ušša in a tablet [and send it here with the first traveller].
a-na É kà-ri-im a-na ša-du-ú-tim a-dí-in ||| I gave to the Colony Office as šaddu'utumšadduātum tax
