i-na tí-tù-ri-im áš-qúl ||| I paid at the bridge
a-na ma-lá-hi-im a-dí-in ||| I paid to the boatman
a-ma-kam a-wa-tí la ta-áš-me-ma i-pí Bu-ṣí-a ša qá-tí ú-kà-lu-šu ha-ra-nam ša-ni-tám i-ta-lá-ak-ma iš-tù Du-ur-hu-mì-it a-na Wa-ah-<šu>-ša-na iš-tù Wa-ah-šu-ša-na a-na Ša-lá-tù-ar i-ta-lá-ak-ma né-nu i-ku-ba-a-tim ni-ir-ta-na-pu-ud ||| Have you not heard there about my affairs from the mouth of Buṣiya? That my hand is holding him? (That) he has left by another route, and has gone from Durhumit to Wahšušana and hence to Šalatuwar, and that we are chasing around after him in the <gap>
i-na 20 GÚ 15 ma-na URUDU ša i-na Wa-ah-šu-ša-na a-šu-mì-a i-ša-qú-lu-ni 10 GÚ 55 ma-na URUDU SIG5 a-na A-šur-ma-lik a-ma-lá té-er-tí-kà ú-sà-ni-iq 10 ma-na ú-ma-am ku-nu-ki-a ak-nu-uk-ma na-áš-a-kum ší-tí URUDU-i-kà 9 GÚ 20 ma-na URUDU ṣú-ha-ri-kà ta-e-ra-ma lu-šé-bi4-la-kum ||| Out of the 20 talents and 15 minas of coppers that they will pay in Wahšušana on my behalf, I handed over 10 talents and 55 minas of good copper to Aššur-malik in accordance with your message. 10 minas I sealed with my seal today, and I am bringing it to you. (As for) the remainder of your copper – 9 talents and 20 minas – return your servant so that he may bring it to you <gap>
1 1/2 ma-na URUDU SIG5 a-na A-lá-hi-im 1 ma-na URUDU SIG5 a-qá-tí-šu 2/3 ma-na URUDU ší-ku-um a-na ra-bi4-ṣí-im 6 GÍN URUDU SIG5 mu-ṣú-šu i-na A-li-a-ša 4 GÍN i-na Da-ša-a É ub-ri-šu a-na-ku-ma a-pu-ul 2/3 ma-na URUDU ta-ší-a-tí-im 1/4 GÍN a-na ša ma-ṣa-ra-tim ú tí-tù-ri-im ||| 1 1/2 minas of good copper for Ali-ahum. 1 mina of good copper at his disposal. 2/3 minas of šikkum-copper for the attorney. 6 shekels of good copper for his mūṣium in Aliašša. I personally balanced 4 shekels (for) his lodgings in Daša. 40 shekels of copper for transporting. 1/4 shekel (of silver) for the guards and the bridge.
1/2 ma-na URUDU SIG5 a-na ub-ru áš-qúl 1 ma-na URUDU SIG5 ag-ra-am a-gu5-ur-ma a-dí tí-tù-ri-im a-dí-šu-um 2 1/2 GÍN AN.NA i-Dí-ša a-wi-lúm lá-pí-it ||| I paid 1/2 minas of good copper for lodgings. I hired a servant and I gave him 1 mina of good copper until the bridge. The man was booked for 2 1/2 shekels of tin in Diša
tí-de8-ma i-na Wa-ah-šu-ša-na ú Ša-lá-tù-ar mu-uš-té-bi-lu KÙ.BABBAR 10 ma-na a-na be-lu KÙ.BABBAR e-pu-šu-ni ||| You know that in Wahšušana and Šalatuwar those who do business realise at least 10 minas of silver for the investors
a-na sà-he-er-tim ša qá-tí-a 5 MA.NA URUDU áš-qúl ||| I paid 5 minas for the sundries that are in my possession.
10 MA.NA [a]-na ag-ri-im [ša] iš-tí-a is-hu-ru [áš-q]úl i-na Wa-áš-ha-ni-a a-dí-šu-um ||| I paid 10 minas for the hireling who was delayed with me. I gave them to him in Wašhaniya.
iš-tù Wa-ah-šu-ša-na a-dí Ša-la-tù-a-ar 1 5/6 MA.NA 5 GÍN.TA URUDU lu da-a-tum lu ú-ku-ul-tí ANŠE lu É ub-ri-im ik-šu-ud-ni-a-tí a-ha-ma ||| From Wahšušana to Šalatuwar 1 5/6 minas 5 shekels came on as fees for donkey fodder and lodgings for each of us.
1/3 MA.NA.TA i-na tí-tù-ri-im i-na ANŠE i-sú-hu ||| In addition, they deducted 1/3 mina for each donkey at the bridge.
