a-wa-tí ša DAM GAL sí-sé-e ma-lá tág-mu-ru té-er-ta-kà lí-lí-kam ||| Let a your message come to me about the agreement you made with the wife of the chief of the horses
1 GÚ 5 MA.NA AN.NA ku-nu-ki ša a-limki 50 TÚG ku-ta-nu qá-áb-li-ú-tum 15 MA.NA AN.NA-ak qá-tim 2 ANŠE.HI.A ṣa-lá-mu ||| 1 talent and 5 minas of tin with the seal of the City (of Assur), 50 kutānumkutānum textiles of average quality, 15 minas of hand-tin and 2 black donkeys
Šu-Be-lúm DUMU Zu-ur-zu-ur li-ip-qí-da-ku-nu-tí-ma [iš]-tí lu-qú-na-tim ša a-wi-lim a-na Pu-ru-uš-ha-dim še-ri-ba-ma a-na i-ta-aṭ-lim dí-na-ma ||| Šu-Belum son of Zurzur will entrust<gap> to you, and you should lead it into Purušhaddum together with the goods of the man and you should sell it for cash upon delivery
AN.NA ša šé-ep Ku-za-ri 5ki-ma e-ru-ba-ni a-na 6Pu-ru-uš-ha-dim uš-té-bi4-il5-šu 7a-na 5 u4-me a-na KÙ.BABBAR 8a-da-ga-al ||| (concerning) the tin transported by Kuzari – when he arrived I sent him to Purušhaddum; in five days I expect the silver.
1/3 MA.NA KÙ.BABBAR iš-tù Ka-ni-iš a-dí Wa-aš-ha-ni-a a-ša bi4-lá-tim a-dí-in 17 1/3 GÍN KÙ.BABBAR iš-tù Wa-aš-ha-ni-a a-dí Ú-lá-ma a-ša bi4-lá-tim ù mu-qá-ri-bi4-a a-dí-in ||| I gave 20 shekels of silver to the porters from Kaneš to Wašhaniya. I gave 17 1/3 shekels of silver to the porters and my escort.
um-ma [šu-n]u-ma ⌈16⌉ li-me-e 40 MA.NA URUDU ší-im SÍG.HI.A A-bu-ša-lim ÌR a-na Ú-ší-na-lam ha-bu-ul 30 li-me-e URUDU ša nam-e-dim ša É.GAL-lúm ha-bu-lu ||| They said: 'They said: the slave Abu-šalim owes 16,040 minas of copper, the price of wool, to Ušinalam. As to the 30,000 minas of copper from the others that the palaces owes <gap>'
a-na Pu-ru-uš-ha-dim a-ṣé-er ru-ba-im GAL ší-i[p-ra-am] i-ša-pár-šu-ma ||| to Purušhaddum concerning the great king his message he sent
šál-ma-ku iš-tù Tí-me-el-ki-na ni-tí-ṣí ||| I am well. I have now left Timelkiya
áš-pu-ra-ku-nu-tí um-ma a-na-ku-ma AN.NA-ki ša bi-lá-tim ag-ra-ma a-na Ni-na-ša-a li-ší-ú-nim a-ša-me-ma a-li-ki a-na Wa-áš-ha-ni-a lá ú-šu-ru šu-ma Wa-ah-šu-ša-na-i-im ù Kà-ni-ší-im ša ma-mì-tám ub-lu-ni-ni ṭup-pí ik-ta-áš-dam i-na sí-ki-im dí-na-ma li-ší-ú-nim ||| I wrote to you, saying: 'Hire some porters to bring my tin to Nenašša'. I hear that they will not set travellers free to go to Wašhaniya. If my letter has reached you (concerning that) they have brought the Wahšušanean and the Kanišite an oath, then give (the tin) in a sikkum so that they can bring it.
3 i-lá-tum 5 GÚ URUDU ma-sí-am šu-qúl-ta-ší-na ku-nu-ki-a kà-ni-ší-ú na-áš-ú-ni-ku-nu-tí 6 GÍN KÙ.BABBAR ig-ri-šu-nu dí-na-šu-nu-tí ù ṣú-ha-ri ša-hi-za-ma ak-lam lu-ša-ki-lu-šu-nu šu-ma AN.NA-ki a-dí-ni lá ta-bu-kà-nim a-na kà-ni-ší-e dí-na iš-tí sí-ki-im li-ši-ú-nim 5 GÍN KÙ.BABBAR ig-ri AN.NA dí-na-šu-nu-tí ù dUTU-tap-pá-i iš-tí-šu-nu li-tal-kam ||| The Kanešites are bringing you 3 sacks of refined copper weighing 5 talents under my seal. Give them their payment of 6 shekels of silver and instruct my servants to give them something to eat. If you haven't yet brought along my tin, then give it to the Kanešites so that they may bring it together with the sikkum. Pay them five shekels of tin as their wages and let Šamaš-tappa'i go with them
a-hi a-ta i-hi-id-ma 20 GÚ URUDU SIG5 šé-bi4-lam Ni-na-ša-i-u[m] sí-kam lá e-pá-ša-am-ma i-na ANŠE.HI.A lu ṣú-ha-ru 1 GÚ.TA ù 2 GÚ li-iz-bi4-lu-nim ||| Dear brother – take care to send me 20 talents of fine copper. The Nenaššean is not going to make a sikkum for me, so let the donkeys or the servants bring one or two talents here
um-ma a-ta-ma 20 GÚ URUDU i-sí-ki-im ni-na-ša-i-um a-dí Wa-áš-ha-ni-a le-pu-ša-am ni-na-ša-i-um sà-ni-iq lá na-ṭù ||| You said: 'Let the Nenaššean produce 20 talents of copper in a sikkum for me as far as Wašhaniya', but the Nenaššean has checked it and it is not feasible, so he will not make a sikkum <gap> a sikkum is not feasible and it will not me made
