[a-na]-kam ru-ba-um [Wa-á]š-ha-na-[i!]-um [i]-li-kam a-na Pu-ru-uš-ha-dim ù Ha-tim ik-ta-lá-ni ||| The king of Wašhaniya came here. He has prevented us from going to Purušhaddum or Hattum.
ṭup-pá-kà i-li-kam-ma a-šu-mì AN.NA 4 GÍN ša Dan-A-šur i-Kà-ni-iš e-zi-bu mì-ma-ša-ma ú-lá ta-al-tap-tám mì-šu ša ki-ma a-wi-lim ra-gi5-im kà-ku-šu il5-qé-ú-ma a-Ku-na-na-me-et i-tal-ku ta-[á]š-pu-ra-am um-ma a-ta-ma a-šu-mì-šu-ma a-H[a]-tim a-pá-ri-kà-ma iš-tí-a a-na Pu-ru-[u]š-ha-dim e-ra-ab-ma ú-za-kà-ma i-pá-nim-ma a-ṭá-ra-da-šu ||| Your letter came, but you wrote nothing at all about the 4 shekels of tin that Dan-Aššur left behind in Kaneš. Why has he taken his weapons like a criminal and gone to Kunana-mit? You wrote, saying: 'Because of him, I am barred from going to Hattum so he will enter Purušhaddum with me, and I will clear myself, and then I will send him to you as fast as possible'.
ší-ma-am šu ra am ša i-dí-ú i-li-bi4-i ma-tí-im ša Ha-tim KÙ.BABBAR šé-bi-lá-ma ší-ma-am lá-áš-a-am-ma ||| the purchase of the <gap> that they know about, send me some money to the libbi mātim of Hattum so that I can make the purchases
