ERÍNMEŠ.HI.A ni-ni-in-ku-wa-an-z[i pa-a-i-š]i [ERÍNMEŠ (ŠA) KUR.KURMEŠ KUR.UGUTIM KUR URUIš-hu-pí-it-ta [KUR URU <gap> (<gap> ) HUR.S]AGŠa-ka[d]-du-nu-wa KUR URUŠa-na-hu-it-ta [KUR URU <gap> (<gap>)] <gap> KUR [U]RUTu-u-pa-az-zi-ia [KUR URULa-h]u-u-wa-za-an-ti-ia KUR URUI-šu-wa [KUR URU <gap> (<gap>)]-<gap>-ia [k]u-[i]t ku-it ŠA KUR.UGUTIM [ERÍ]NMEŠ.HI.A na-aš hu-u-ma-an-du-uš ni-ni-i[k] ||| You will go to set the troop contingents moving. [The troops of the lan]ds: the Upper Land, the land of Ishupitta, [the land of GN], the Moun[tain] of Sakaddunuwa, the land of Sanahwitta, [the land of GN], the land of Tupaziya, [the land of Lah]uwazantiya, the land of Isuwa, [the land of <gap>]-iya – what so ever troop contingents of the Upper Lands there are [therein] – set them all in motion.
GÍR ša A-šùr ||| dagger of Aššur
3 GÍN KÙ.BABBAR a-É ub-ri i-na Pu-ru-uš-ha-dim a-dí-in ||| 3 shekels of silver for my lodgings in Purušhaddum
