a-na A-sur-e-mu-qi qi-bi-ma um-ma Ma-:jf-i-li-ma 4 GU AN.NA u it-ra-su ku-nu-ki sa A-limk; na-as-a-kum 2 me-at u 50 TUG.HI.A sA.BA 20 TUG.HI.A SIGS 17 TUG.HI.A SIGS sa ik-ri-bi-kG l3 e-ma-ru !)a-la-mu mi-ma a-ni~l a-ra-de8-a-kum lu-qu-ut-ka sal-rna-at e-ma-ru-ka sal-mu-it mi-ma li-ba~ka la,i-pa-ri-id i-hi-id-ma 1 ma-na KU.BABBAR a-pa-ni-a a-na Ha-hi-im !ie-bi-lam su-ma a-bi4 a-ta sa 5 GlN KU.BABBAR sa-ha-ar-tam sa-a-rna i-ku-nu-ki-kG : ku-nu-uk-ma a-pa-ni-a se-bi-lam i-na E-lu-hu-ut ni-ta-:ja-am ||| To Assur-emuqi from Ma~i-ili. I am carrying 4 talents of tin and extras sealed in the City. 250 textiles- thereof 20 textiles of good quality, and 17 textiles of good quality belonging to your ikribum- as well as 13 black donkeys, all of this I am bringing to you. Your goods are well. Your donkeys are well. Do not worry about a thing. Take care and send I mina of silver in advance of me to Hahhum. If you are my father, buy 5 shekels of silver worth of small goods, seal it with your seal, and send it to me. We have just left Eluhhut.
