1 a-na dIM-ANDUL 2 oi-bi-ma um-ma 3 Su-Be-lum-ma URUDU-a-kd 4 1 ma-na 12 1/2 GÍN.TA 5 a-na KB to-di-in 6 ANSE.HI.A a-na 7 62 ma-na URUDU to-di-in 8 a-ma-la té-er-tt-kd 9 URUDU-i al-qe 10 2 ma-na URUDU DIRI 11 a-di i-zi-zu-<ni> 12 a-na SE-im u ti-ib-nim 13 as-qul ||| Speak to Adad-sulùli, thus (says) Sú-Bèlim: your copper has been sold at a rate of 72 1/2 shekels of copper per shekel of silver, the donkeys (sold) for 62 minas of copper. In accordance with your instructions I took my (share of the) copper. I paid 2 minas of excellent copper for barley and straw as long as (the donkeys) were standing.
1 kd-ru-um Wa-ah-su-sa-na 2 sa-he-er GAL 3 di-nain i-di-ma 4 ITU.KAM té-i-na-tim 5 li-mu-um Su-Su-in 6 DUMU Ba-bi-lim fu-ma 7 URUDU sa dIM-ANDUL 8 Ba-al-Iil-a 9 i-na Sa-lk-ta-ar 10 is-ba-at ||| The plenary session of the kàrum of WahsuAana passed this verdict: date: month 10, year-eponym Sú-Suen son of Babulum; if Baltua has taken copper beloaging to Adad-sulitli in Salatuar (Adad-sulúli will present his terms and they will produce their witnesses).
1 dIM-su-lu-li 2 at Ba-al-Iû-a i-na 3 mì-ig-•a-ti-su-nu 4 is-bu-tit-ni-a-ti-ma 5 um-ma dIM-ANDUL-ma 6 a-na Ba-al-Iù-a-ma 7 5 1/2 GÚ URUDU ma-si-am 8 i-na Sa-la-td-ar 9 is-ti dUTU-e-nam 10 kd-sa-ri-a 11 ta-ak-la-a 12 su-ma URUDU a-na 13 URUDU-i-a i-tit-ar 14 1/2 ma-na.TA ù 15 1 GÍN.TA KB a-ma-la 16 di-in kd-ri-im 17 to-sa-qk-lam ||| In mutual agreement Adad-sulúlf and Baltua seized us, and Adad-sulúli said to Baltua: "You withheld in Salatuar 5 1/2 talents of refined copper from my transporter Samas-ennam. If it is proved that this copper is mine, you will pay me (silver for my copper) at a rate of 30 shekels of copper per shekel of silver, in accordance with the kârum verdict."
