a-na A-la-hi-im DUMU Ma-nu-a qi-bi-ma um-ma Ta-ha-sa-li-ma 5 GÚ 10 ma-na URUDU ma-si-lam a-di-na-kum um-ma a-ta-ma KB 1 GÍN lu-sé-li-a-kum a-ta KB a-na Kd-ni-is ta-ta-ba-al a-hi a-ta su-ma si-ma-am sa ba-Id-li-a Ia ta-ds-a-ma-am si-ma-am sa ta-ks-1d'-mu se-big-lam su-ma KB i-ba-si KB a-na A-sur-DÙG di-in ||| Speak to Alahum son of Mannua, thus (says) Tahasa(i)li: I gave 5 talents 10 minas of refined copper to you. You said: "I will earn for you the silver, every shekel (of it)." But you have just moved the silver to Kanish! My dear brother, if you did not buy profitable merchandise for me, send me whatever you bought. If silver is left over, give it to Asur-tâb.
