lu a-wi-ld-ti ki-ma a-wi-[lu-ti]-kd KB 10 ma-na pd-ni-am-ma sa te-pu-su ab-kd-ma ma-a§-kd-ta-kd a-na a-limki ku-su-ud URUDU sa i-a-ti ú Su-A-siir sa i-na E.GAL-lim ur-da-ni a-ta i2 sa ki-ma A-su[r-] a-na KB di-na-su-ma [ku-u]n-kd-ma se-[bi-la-nim] ||| Be a man and act accordingly by sending me the first silver, 10 minas, you acquire, and let your cash comse to the City. You and Assur-[ Is agent must sell my and Sù-Asur's copper that came down from the palace for silver and send (it) to me uader seal.
a-di URUDU.sa A-mur-!star a-na sa ki i-a-ti URUDU i-na Pu-ru-us-ha-tim ta-da-nam ú-la i-mu-/u ha-ra-ni.a-na [P]u-ru-us-ha-tim i-na u4-mì-im tup-pt-i ta-sa-me-u na-as-am A-anur-!star ú Lu-lu URUDU li di nu nim ma KB i-pk-ni-a lu-se-si-a-ku-um ||| As for Amur-Istar's copper: he refused to hand it over to my representatives in Purushattum. I will set out for Purushattum; on the very day you read my letter, I will be on my way! I hope that Amur-Istar and Lulu will meet me and give me the copper; I will personally send you the silver.
