dumu a-šùr šu-um-šu kù.gi a-na a-ki-dí-im a-mu-ri-im ù šu-bi-ri-im ma-ma-an la i-da-an ša i-du-nu ú-lá i-ba-lá-aṭ ||| no Assyrian whatever shall give gold to an Akkadian, an Amorite, or a Shubarean. Whoever does so shall not remain alive
