iš-tù ta-li-kà-ni i-na é a-bi-a qá-dí a-ma-tim ta-kà-al ú ta-ša-tí ú a-ma-kam 5 ṣa-bu-um e-ba-ru-tí-ni ša pá-du-ga-ni-kà i-na é-tí-ni iš-ta-tí-ú-ni i-na wa-ar-ki-tim a-ša-tám ta-hu-úz-ma 2 gín kb ù 1 baneš.ta gig ku-a-tí a-ta-dí-na-kum ||| Since you came here, you are eating and drinking in my father's house together with the slave girls And there five of our colleagues, belonging to your padugannum, have all been drinking at our house. Later on, you married a wife and I regularly gave you 2 shekels of silver and 1 ṣimid of wheat.
kb ša i-a-tí i-lá-kà-ni a-na é pì-lá-ah-ištar iš-ta-aq-lu-šu ú qá-tám ša a-šùr-na-da a-na é a-limki a-na hu-bu-li-šu iš-ta-aq-lu-šu a-na-kam kb 1 gín a-na ba-lá-ṭí-ni lá-šu-m[a] ṣú-ùh-ru-um i-na bu-bu- ||| silver of mine which you owe: it was spent on the house of Pilah-Ishtar and also silver of Ashur-nada: it was spent on the house in the town for his provisions: now: 1 shekel of silver for my sustenance
i-na kb 1 gín áš-ra-ni-ma igi a-šùr ì-lí-a : lá-ak-ru-ba-kum ||| Help me with a shekel of silver and I will pray on your behalf in front of my god Aššur
išti ālikim panîmma ṭurdaššu ||| accompanied by a member of the firm or would go accompanied by other travellers
