a-na Šu-İštar qí-bi-ma um-ma A-šùr-GAL ú LUGAL-Sú-en6-ma lá ta-áš-ta-na-me-e ki-ma / URUDU SİG5 ma-ah-ṣú-ni ší-i-<im> / URUDU lá i-ba-ší ú ma-tum / a-na e-bu-ri-šu i-ṭí-hi-ma ub-ru-um lá-šu / i-na ma-qá-at ub-ri / URUDU ni-da-an-ma LUGAL-Sú-en6 i-ta-lá-kam ||| To Šu-Ištar, speak! Thus says Assur-GAL and king-his: you are not sending? Since quality copper (its price?) has fallen, there is no copper trade. Furthermore, the country has approached harvest and there is no foreigner here. When a foreigner comes, we will sell copper and Šarrum-Su'en (will go there).
wa-áb-ru lá-šu i-ma-qá-at wa-áb-ri lu KÙ.BABBAR lu KÙ.Kİ a-ša-a-ma ú-šé-ba-lá-am ||| (Here) there is no foreigner. When a foreigner comes, I will buy either silver or gold and bring (it).
A[N.N]A [(<gap>)] ša šé-ep Dam-qá-[a (<gap>)] ub-ru-ú lá-šu-ma [(<gap>)] lá ta-dí-in ||| tin (under) Damqa's administration (there) was no foreigners (to buy) it, so it was not sold.
a-na Šu-İštar qí-bi-ma um-ma A-šùr-GAL ú LUGAL-Sú-en6-ma lá ta-áš-ta-na-me-e ki-ma URUDU SİG5 ma-ah-ṣú-ni ší-i-<im> URUDU lá i-ba-ší ú ma-tum a-na e-bu-ri-šu i-ṭí-hi-ma ub-ru-um lá-šu i-na ma-qá-at ub-ri URUDU ni-da-an-ma LUGAL-Sú-en6 i-ta-lá-kam ||| To Šu-Ištar say: Thus speaks Aššur-GAL and Šarrum-Su'en: You are not providing (it). Since good copper is falling in price, there is no copper trade. Also the country is near harvest and there is no foreigner here. When the foreigner comes, we will sell the copper and Šarrum-Su'en will come (there).
wa-áb-ru lá-šu i-ma-qá-at wa-áb-ri lu KÙ.BABBAR lu KÙ.Kİ a-ša-a-ma ú-šé-ba-lá-am ||| (When) the foreigner comes, (if there is) no foreigner, I will buy either silver or gold and bring (it).
