su-ma a-na Ha-hi-im ta-pa-la-ah, a-na Ur-su-ma a-li-ik, a pu-tum a pu-tum we di-kà-ma, a-li-ik is-ti ELLAT, a-na Ma-ma la té-ra-ab, ù ma-la té-er-ti, a-lim' ELLAT" a-hi-kà, a-na sal-si-îu, li pè-er-sù-ma pà-ni-ù-um, i-Ma-ma lu-si-ma a-na, ma-at Kà-ni-iî, ik-ku-du sa-ni-um, i-na Ur-su lu-si, ù sa-li-iî-tum, ki-a-ma lu-si ||| If you fear (to go) to Hahhum, (then) go rather to Ursu. I beg you, please, go there alone! You must not enter Mâma with the caravan, and according to the instructions (of the authorities) of the City (of Assur), your brother's caravan must be divided into three: the first (convoy) must depart from Mâma, and (when) it has reached the land of Kanis, the second (convoy) must depart from Ursu, and the third (convoy) must depart in the same manner.
i-tu : uq me-e ma-du'-[tim], a-ta-sa-ab a-na kà-ri-im, i-hi-id-ma : lé-ma ku-[si-im], là-tal-kam-ma ||| Now for many days I am stuck here. That said, I intend to go to the kârum (of Kanis) before winter.
ku-sù-um, ma-ad : e-ma-ru-um, a-na a-lé-ki-im, là na-tù-ù ||| Snow is very heavy and the donkeys cannot move forward.
