ma-na kù.babbar ṣa-ru-pá-am i-ṣé-er Šu-mì-a-bi4-a E-lá-ma i-šu iš-tù ha-muš-tim ša dingir-na-da 1 gín.ta ṣí-ib-tám i-itu.1.kam ú-ṣa-áb itu.1.kam bé-el-tí-é.gal-lim li-mu-um puzur4-dmuš ||| Šumi-abiya owes Elamma 1⁄2 mina refined silver. He will add as interest 1 shekel per mina per month from the week of Ili-nāda.
ma-na 5 gín kù.babbar ṣa-ru-pá-am i-ṣé-er A-šur-ta-nak-lá-ku ú A-mur-dingir A-šur-ta-ak-lá-ku i-šu iš-tù ha-muš-tim ša En-nam-A-šur itu.kam be-el-tí-é.gal-lim li-mu-um Il5-šu-gal dumu [Ba]-zi 2 gín.ta a-ma-na-im i-na itu.1.kam-im ṣí-ib-tám ú-ṣa-áb ||| Aššur-taklāku and Amur-ilī owe Aššur-taklāku 1 mina 5 shekels refined silver. They (lit. he) will add as interest 2 shekels per mina per month from the week of Ennam-Aššur.
ma-na kù.babbar ṣa-ru-pá-am i-ṣé-er puzur4-A-na Šu-Be-lúm i-šu iš-tù ha-mu-uš-tim ša A-šur-ma-lik ù I-na-a 11⁄2 g[ín.ta] ṣí-ib-[tám i-na] itu.kam [a-na ma-na]-im ú-ṣa-áb ˹itu.kam˺ be-<el>-tí-kál-lim li-mu-um A-šur-na-da Pu-šu-ke-en6 qá-ta-ta-tum ||| Puzur-Anna owes Šū-Bēlum 25⁄6 minas refined silver. He will add 11⁄2 shekels as interest per month per mina from the week of Aššur-mālik and Innaya.
Wa-al-dí-lúm dumu Šu-Be-lim a-na En-na-Sú-en6 dumu A-šur-ni-šu ù me-er-e-šu a-na mì-ma šu-um-šu [ú-lá] i-tù-ru-ú itu.kam be-el-tí-é.gal-lim li-mu-um En-na-Sú-en6 dumu Šu-A-šur ||| Waldi-lum s. Šū-Bēlum must not return to Enna-Suen s. Aššur-nīšu or his children for anything.
ma-na kù.babbar i-ṣé-er Ha-zu-ba-lá Šu-Be-lúm i-šu iš-tù ha-mu-uš-tim ša Pu-šu-ke-en6 ù Zu-pá itu.1.kam ša sà-ra-tim 15 gín a-na [ṣí-ba]-at ni-ga-lim i-ša-qal [15 g]ín a-na [ša] A-na i-ša-qal [1]⁄2 ma-na a-na da-áš-e i-ša-qal šu-ma lá ìš-qú-ul a-na 1 ma-na-im 3 gín.ta ú-ṣa-áb li-mu-um A-šur-sig5 ||| Hazubala owes Šū-Bēlum 1 mina silver. From the week of Pūšu-kēn and Zupa (in) Month II, he will pay 15 shekels silver at harvest. He will pay back 15 shekels at the festival of Anna. He will pay (the remaining) 1⁄2 mina back in the spring. If he does not pay (by then), he will add 3 shekels per mina per month.
