takku ARAD LÚ uruHATTI IŠTU KUR Luwiyaz LÚ uruHATTI kuiski tāyizzi nℵan ANA KUR uruHATTI uwatezzi ishasℵsisℵan ganeszi nuℵssi 12 GÍN KÙ.BABBAR pāi parnaℵssēℵa suwayizzi ||| If a Hittite man abducts a male slave belonging to a(nother) Hittite man from the land of Luviya and leads him here to the land of Hatti, and his owner recognizes him, (the abductor) shall pay him 12 shekels of silver, and he shall look to his house for it
uizzi nu ANA LÚ.[ŠUKUR.GUŠKIN?]li [kiss]an ||| comes and calls to the [gold-spear-?]man in [Hittite?] thus
