ehu dAMAR.UTU kattiℵtiℵmaℵtta dInnarawantas(!) uwaᲟnᲠdu ēshanuwanta kuyēs wēssaᲟnᲠta lú.mešLūlahiyasℵsan huprus kuyēs ishiyantis ||| Come, Santa! Let the Innarawant-deities come with you, who wear bloodied (clothes), who have tied up Lulahiyan belts
dŠa-an-ta-aš LUGAL-uš dAn-na-ru-um-mi-en-zi aš-ha-nu-wa-an-ta ku-in-zi wa-aš-ša-an-ta-ri dLu-u-la-hi-in-za-aš-tar hu-u-up-pa-ra-za ku-in-zi hi-iš-hi-ya-an-ti ||| Santa, the king, the Innarawant-deities come with you, who wear bloodied (clothes), who have tied up Lulahiyan belts
arahzenas KUR.KUR.(MEŠ) lúKÚR ||| foreign inimical lands
