nℵat katta DUMU-KA DUMU.DUMU-KA harzi ULℵatℵsiyℵatℵkan arha danzi ||| Your son (and) your grandson will hold it after (you). One will not take it away from him
ANŠE.KUR.RA.MEŠ KARAŠℵyaℵtta kuin ŠA KUR ídHūlaya I-NA uruHATTI É tuppas harzi nℵanℵsi ABUℵYA mHattusilis arha pissiat ||| The horses and the troops that the Office of the Hulaya river-land has (registered) for you(!) in Hatti, my father Hattusili has canceled for him this (obligation)
